## 2026-03-28 - useSetMergeSplit.ts merge/split undo callbacks use raw fetch with no error handling
- The undo restore callbacks in both merge and split already threw errors on failure, but `useUndo.executeUndo` (and `executeRedo`) had no catch handler — errors became unhandled promise rejections invisible to the user
- Added `onError` callback parameter to `useUndo()`, with a stable ref to avoid re-renders. `executeUndo` and `executeRedo` now catch errors from restore/redo callbacks and surface them via `onError`
- Wired `setErrorToast` from `useToastStack` as the `onError` handler in `App.tsx` (reordered hook calls so `useToastStack` precedes `useUndo`)

